---
/**
 * Horizon (DESIGN.md §7b) - a soft section-boundary cue: a 1px hairline that
 * fades to nothing at both edges, centred, that the page light flows across.
 * Decorative (aria-hidden) and deliberately VERY faint - a gentle boundary, not
 * a hard rule. Placed between body sections; dial the alpha/placement back if it
 * ever starts to read as ruled blocks.
 */
---

<div class="horizon" aria-hidden="true"></div>

<style>
  .horizon {
    max-width: 1320px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(
      90deg,
      transparent,
      rgba(241, 239, 234, 0.11) 50%,
      transparent
    );
  }
</style>
